ngland":"英國英格蘭格盧斯特斯爾","lifeSummary":"David Brooke於大約1446年出生在英國格盧斯特斯爾布里斯托。他於1473年與Johanna Joan Amerike在英國英格蘭格盧斯特斯爾結婚。他們至少是1個女兒的父母。他去世於1522年12月25日在他的家鄉享年77歲，埋葬在英國英格蘭布里斯托雷可利福。"},"zh-hans":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"大约1446年–1522年12月25日","1452–1538":"1452年–1538年","1495–1553":"1495年–1553年","1446–1522":"1446年–1522年","1446":"1446年","1522":"1522年","1455":"1455年","1553":"1553年","25 DEC 1522":"1522年12月25日","1452":"1452年","1473":"1473年","1495":"1495年","ABT 1446":"大约1446年","1538":"1538年","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"英国英格兰布里斯托雷可利福","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"英国格盧斯特斯爾布里斯托","England":"英国","Gloucestershire, England":"英国英格兰格盧斯特斯爾","lifeSummary":"David Brooke于大约1446年出生在英国格盧斯特斯爾布里斯托。他于1473年与Johanna Joan Amerike在英国英格兰格盧斯特斯爾结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。他去世于1522年12月25日在他的家乡享年77岁，埋葬在英国英格兰布里斯托雷可利福。"},"hr":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"oko 1446.–25. prosinca 1522.","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495.–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522.","1446":"1446","1522":"1522.","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25. prosinca 1522.","1452":"1452","1473":"1473.","1495":"1495.","ABT 1446":"oko 1446.","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, Engleska, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"okolo 1446–25. prosince 1522","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522","1446":"1446","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25. prosince 1522","1452":"1452","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","ABT 1446":"okolo 1446","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, Anglie, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, Anglie","England":"Anglie","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"omkring 1446–25. december 1522","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522","1446":"1446","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25. december 1522","1452":"1452","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","ABT 1446":"omkring 1446","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, England, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"circa 1446–25 december 1522","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522","1446":"1446","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25 december 1522","1452":"1452","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","ABT 1446":"circa 1446","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"about 1446–25 December 1522","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522","1446":"1446","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25 December 1522","1452":"1452","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","ABT 1446":"about 1446","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, England, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Brooke","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Brook  , which preserves a trace of the Old English dative singular case, originally used after a preposition (e.g. ‘at the brook’).","History: In 1650, Robert and Mary Mainwaring Brooke brought ten children and a number of servants with them from England to MD, where Robert became governor. Although the fourteen known contemporary Brooke immigrants in VA included Robert's brothers Richard and Humphrey, the relationships of the others are unknown. Brooke family memorials remain in the Anglican church at Whitchurch, Hampshire, England."],"variants":[{"name":"Brook","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived by a brook, stream, water-meadows or low, marshy ground, from Middle English <i>brook</i>, Old English <i>brōc</i> ‘brook, stream’; or a habitational name from any of various places called with this word, such as Brook (Kent, Rutland) or Brooke (Norfolk).","North German: topographic name for someone who lived by a water meadow or marsh, from Low German <i>brook</i> (cognate with German   Bruch   ‘swamp’ and Old English <i>brōc</i>; see 1 above).","Americanized form of Dutch <b>Broek</b>: topographic name from <i>broek</i>, a cognate of 2 above."]}]},{"name":"David","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":9,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"David Brooke was born about 1446, in Bristol, Gloucestershire, England. He married Johanna Joan Amerike in 1473, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 25 December 1522, in his hometown, at the age of 77, and was buried in Redcliffe, Bristol, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"umbes 1446–25. detsember 1522","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522","1446":"1446","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25. detsember 1522","1452":"1452","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","ABT 1446":"umbes 1446","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1446–25 DEC 1522":"noin 1446–25. joulukuuta 1522","1452–1538":"1452–1538","1495–1553":"1495–1553","1446–1522":"1446–1522","1446":"1446","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1553":"1553","25 DEC 1522":"25. joulukuuta 1522","1452":"1452","1473":"1473","1495":"1495","ABT 1446":"noin 1446","1538":"1538","Redcliffe, Bristol Unitary Authority, Bristol, England":"Redcliffe, Bristol, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bristol, Gloucestershire, England":"Bristol, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England","Gloucestershire, England":"Glouceste